# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithWarrior2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah woke up early the next day."
    new "Sarah woke up early the next day."

    old "Next to her, Samayra was still sound asleep."
    new "Next to her, Samayra was still sound asleep."

    old "Watching her like this, she seemed even more vulnerable than she usually did."
    new "Watching her like this, she seemed even more vulnerable than she usually did."

    old "Sarah decided to let her sleep in."
    new "Sarah decided to let her sleep in."

    old "Most of the soldiers were still asleep, sleeping off whatever hungover they inflicted on themselves in celebration."
    new "Most of the soldiers were still asleep, sleeping off whatever hungover they inflicted on themselves in celebration."

    old "She walked through the camp, inspecting it."
    new "She walked through the camp, inspecting it."

    old "Shoddy work preparing the tent. Disorganized storage of weapons. Unprotected supply wagons."
    new "Shoddy work preparing the tent. Disorganized storage of weapons. Unprotected supply wagons."

    old "The whole thing was a mess, but after the breakdown of morale in the desert, it was a miracle any work got done at all."
    new "The whole thing was a mess, but after the breakdown of morale in the desert, it was a miracle any work got done at all."

    old "She had just begun her rounds when she noticed a man stride across the square towards her."
    new "She had just begun her rounds when she noticed a man stride across the square towards her."

    old "He walked in long steps, his broad shoulders jutting out as though he wanted the world to notice him."
    new "He walked in long steps, his broad shoulders jutting out as though he wanted the world to notice him."

    old "A flawless face, an easy smile and a casual confidence made it hard not to notice him."
    new "A flawless face, an easy smile and a casual confidence made it hard not to notice him."

    old "Hail, Rose knight."
    new "Hail, Rose knight."

    old "Sarah watched as the man performed a Mythran greeting, striking his fist against his chest."
    new "Sarah watched as the man performed a Mythran greeting, striking his fist against his chest."

    old "Greetings."
    new "Greetings."

    old "Her own Rosannan manners seemed small and ordinary compared to their ceremony."
    new "Her own Rosannan manners seemed small and ordinary compared to their ceremony."

    old "How do you know who I am?"
    new "How do you know who I am?"

    old "The man smiled, his white teeth stood in sharp contrast to his bronzed skin."
    new "The man smiled, his white teeth stood in sharp contrast to his bronzed skin."

    old "Your reputation proceeds you."
    new "Your reputation proceeds you."

    old "And when I was told to seek out the Rose Knight, a beautiful woman with golden hair...well, there aren't a lot of those around."
    new "And when I was told to seek out the Rose Knight, a beautiful woman with golden hair...well, there aren't a lot of those around."

    old "He offered up flattery cheaply, it annoyed her."
    new "He offered up flattery cheaply, it annoyed her."

    old "Where I come from, one introduces themselves before presuming to know the other."
    new "Where I come from, one introduces themselves before presuming to know the other."

    old "My apologies, a humble slave such as myself is a stranger to your ways."
    new "My apologies, a humble slave such as myself is a stranger to your ways."

    old "The man bowed low, almost in a mocking fashion."
    new "The man bowed low, almost in a mocking fashion."

    old "I am Cassius, War-Brother to Dio, and slave to house Adamos."
    new "I am Cassius, War-Brother to Dio, and slave to house Adamos."

    old "My master has requested your presence."
    new "My master has requested your presence."

    old "Sarah observed the man for a moment."
    new "Sarah observed the man for a moment."

    old "Your master?"
    new "Your master?"

    old "Yes, the overseer for this entire expedition in fact. They wish to meet with you."
    new "Yes, the overseer for this entire expedition in fact. They wish to meet with you."

    old "Sarah didn't know what to make of it. She had plenty of work to do, but refusing would likely appear rude."
    new "Sarah didn't know what to make of it. She had plenty of work to do, but refusing would likely appear rude."

    old "What if I don't want to meet with your master?"
    new "What if I don't want to meet with your master?"

    old "Cassius shrugged."
    new "Cassius shrugged."

    old "Then I shall report back as such. There is no force here."
    new "Then I shall report back as such. There is no force here."

    old "Despite her reservations, Sarah couldn't help but be intrigued. Perhaps the master of which Cassius spoke could have answers for her."
    new "Despite her reservations, Sarah couldn't help but be intrigued. Perhaps the master of which Cassius spoke could have answers for her."

    old "Fine, I will meet with your master, take me to him."
    new "Fine, I will meet with your master, take me to him."

    old "Excellent, follow me and I will take you to the master's tent."
    new "Excellent, follow me and I will take you to the master's tent."

    old "Sarah walked up besides Cassius and began to follow him."
    new "Sarah walked up besides Cassius and began to follow him."

    old "Looking over the man, Sarah found it hard to wrap her mind around him."
    new "Looking over the man, Sarah found it hard to wrap her mind around him."

    old "Slaves, in her mind, were often weak and servile in appearance. Either broken by their masters or broken by themselves."
    new "Slaves, in her mind, were often weak and servile in appearance. Either broken by their masters or broken by themselves."

    old "This man appeared neither."
    new "This man appeared neither."

    old "You said you are a slave?"
    new "You said you are a slave?"

    old "Cassius nodded."
    new "Cassius nodded."

    old "You do not strike me as one."
    new "You do not strike me as one."

    old "He smiled as he pulled back his tunic, revealing a small scar of pink flesh, running across his chest. A symbol, though Sarah could not tell what it was."
    new "He smiled as he pulled back his tunic, revealing a small scar of pink flesh, running across his chest. A symbol, though Sarah could not tell what it was."

    old "From birth, me and my War-Sister Dio have been raised in service to the Mythran empire."
    new "From birth, me and my War-Sister Dio have been raised in service to the Mythran empire."

    old "We have been in service to various houses over the years, but house Adamos has treated us well these last six years."
    new "We have been in service to various houses over the years, but house Adamos has treated us well these last six years."

    old "You carry yourself as a free man."
    new "You carry yourself as a free man."

    old "Perhaps. I have never known another life, and so perhaps I cannot envy a freedom I never had to begin with."
    new "Perhaps. I have never known another life, and so perhaps I cannot envy a freedom I never had to begin with."

    old "In Mythra, the nature of slavery is also not as crude as most parts of the world."
    new "In Mythra, the nature of slavery is also not as crude as most parts of the world."

    old "One can carve out a space for themselves, to a degree."
    new "One can carve out a space for themselves, to a degree."

    old "It troubled Sarah to hear a man speak of an institution like slavery, as if it was anything other than barbaric."
    new "It troubled Sarah to hear a man speak of an institution like slavery, as if it was anything other than barbaric."

    old "Especially as a victim of it, she assumed he should have known better."
    new "Especially as a victim of it, she assumed he should have known better."

    old "Where I come from, there are no slaves."
    new "Where I come from, there are no slaves."

    old "Except for kings and emperors, we are all slaves to someone or something. All burdened with our own labors and tasks."
    new "Except for kings and emperors, we are all slaves to someone or something. All burdened with our own labors and tasks."

    old "I have found mine to be to my suiting, so who am I to object?"
    new "I have found mine to be to my suiting, so who am I to object?"

    old "And what are your labors, exactly?"
    new "And what are your labors, exactly?"

    old "She watched as the palm of his hands cupped the shaft of his weapon."
    new "She watched as the palm of his hands cupped the shaft of his weapon."

    old "A soldier, much like you I suppose."
    new "A soldier, much like you I suppose."

    old "He seemed proud when he said it."
    new "He seemed proud when he said it."

    old "Oathsworn to my War-Sister. Together we've managed to make our way through life."
    new "Oathsworn to my War-Sister. Together we've managed to make our way through life."

    old "Sarah observed the man as he spoke."
    new "Sarah observed the man as he spoke."

    old "What exactly is that? A...War-Brother, War-Sister?"
    new "What exactly is that? A...War-Brother, War-Sister?"

    old "Cassius turned to face her, smiling his same broad and winning smile."
    new "Cassius turned to face her, smiling his same broad and winning smile."

    old "Aah, forgive me. I forget sometimes that not all hail from Mythra."
    new "Aah, forgive me. I forget sometimes that not all hail from Mythra."

    old "Suddenly, Cassius stopped and gestured."
    new "Suddenly, Cassius stopped and gestured."

    old "But I fear we are out of time, Rose Knight."
    new "But I fear we are out of time, Rose Knight."

    old "Sarah saw he pointed towards the entrance of a large tent, standing out apart from the others in both size and opulence."
    new "Sarah saw he pointed towards the entrance of a large tent, standing out apart from the others in both size and opulence."

    old "Will you tell me another time?"
    new "Will you tell me another time?"

    old "Should we chance to meet again."
    new "Should we chance to meet again."

    old "Now please, my master is waiting for you."
    new "Now please, my master is waiting for you."

    old "He gestured towards the tent's entrance again."
    new "He gestured towards the tent's entrance again."

    old "Sarah made a small bow, thanking Cassius for his escort, and walked towards the commander's tent."
    new "Sarah made a small bow, thanking Cassius for his escort, and walked towards the commander's tent."

    old "As she entered the tent, Sarah instantly felt the comforting shade come across her."
    new "As she entered the tent, Sarah instantly felt the comforting shade come across her."

    old "The heat of the desert seemed distant here."
    new "The heat of the desert seemed distant here."

    old "A mixture of scented spice weighed heavily on the air."
    new "A mixture of scented spice weighed heavily on the air."

    old "As Sarah breathed in the scent, a memory overcame her."
    new "As Sarah breathed in the scent, a memory overcame her."

    old "She had smelled this before."
    new "She had smelled this before."

    old "Sarah remembered the person only a moment before the voice came."
    new "Sarah remembered the person only a moment before the voice came."

    old "So it really is you."
    new "So it really is you."

    old "Sarah quickly turned to the other end of the tent."
    new "Sarah quickly turned to the other end of the tent."

    old "Sitting on the far end of it, behind a large desk covered in scrolls and parchments, sat a woman all too familiar, from a lifetime ago."
    new "Sitting on the far end of it, behind a large desk covered in scrolls and parchments, sat a woman all too familiar, from a lifetime ago."

    old "Casually leaning back in her chair, lady Carolyn smiled at her as if hiding a secret."
    new "Casually leaning back in her chair, lady Carolyn smiled at her as if hiding a secret."

    old "For a moment, Sarah had not the words to speak."
    new "For a moment, Sarah had not the words to speak."

    old "Lady Carolyn pushed herself from her chair and walked up closer to her."
    new "Lady Carolyn pushed herself from her chair and walked up closer to her."

    old "Her eyes moved across her body like a butcher judging a cow."
    new "Her eyes moved across her body like a butcher judging a cow."

    old "A little roughed up here and there, but you still have your mother's beauty."
    new "A little roughed up here and there, but you still have your mother's beauty."

    old "She smiled at Sarah."
    new "She smiled at Sarah."

    old "And now your father's strength as well, I see."
    new "And now your father's strength as well, I see."

    old "Sarah could feel herself falling back years into herself. Rosanna suddenly felt near to her heart."
    new "Sarah could feel herself falling back years into herself. Rosanna suddenly felt near to her heart."

    old "How did you..."
    new "How did you..."

    old "Lady Carolyn turned her head."
    new "Lady Carolyn turned her head."

    old "Survive?"
    new "Survive?"

    old "Ooh dear, my family has always played the odds of the market, and the odds of life."
    new "Ooh dear, my family has always played the odds of the market, and the odds of life."

    old "When you dissapeared, the reports of the advancing tribesmen increased with each passing day."
    new "When you dissapeared, the reports of the advancing tribesmen increased with each passing day."

    old "We considered it a wise moment to...visit some distant relatives in Rahayal."
    new "We considered it a wise moment to...visit some distant relatives in Rahayal."

    old "Sarah could see in her eyes that despite her casual attitude, the memories of Rosanna haunted her too."
    new "Sarah could see in her eyes that despite her casual attitude, the memories of Rosanna haunted her too."

    old "My family made our fortune in banking. For us, we could make our money as easily in one place as another."
    new "My family made our fortune in banking. For us, we could make our money as easily in one place as another."

    old "It was many of the other noble families that could not imagine running from all their holdings."
    new "It was many of the other noble families that could not imagine running from all their holdings."

    old "Many of them died trying to defend plots of land that now run barren. Such a waste of human life, that whole affair."
    new "Many of them died trying to defend plots of land that now run barren. Such a waste of human life, that whole affair."

    old "Lady Carolyn straightened her back and faced Sarah with her steely eyes."
    new "Lady Carolyn straightened her back and faced Sarah with her steely eyes."

    old "Whatever moments of weakness had possessed her, was now banished."
    new "Whatever moments of weakness had possessed her, was now banished."

    old "But tell me dear, I really should be asking you that question."
    new "But tell me dear, I really should be asking you that question."

    old "What question?"
    new "What question?"

    old "How you managed to survive at all. I thought you were dead for years."
    new "How you managed to survive at all. I thought you were dead for years."

    old "Dead?"
    new "Dead?"

    old "Well, you had vanished from the castle and not a soul seemed to have any hint of you."
    new "Well, you had vanished from the castle and not a soul seemed to have any hint of you."

    old "Many of us first suspected your brother had send you away, to hide in some secret fort until the threat of the tribesmen had passed."
    new "Many of us first suspected your brother had send you away, to hide in some secret fort until the threat of the tribesmen had passed."

    old "But your brother was always honest to a fault. We all quickly saw that the panic on his face was no pretend."
    new "But your brother was always honest to a fault. We all quickly saw that the panic on his face was no pretend."

    old "Sarah felt her heart sink, and barely by a moment, prevented herself from breaking into tears."
    new "Sarah felt her heart sink, and barely by a moment, prevented herself from breaking into tears."

    old "Thomas...he...was afraid?"
    new "Thomas...he...was afraid?"

    old "Sarah felt Lady Carolyn's hand on her shoulder."
    new "Sarah felt Lady Carolyn's hand on her shoulder."

    old "Dear, do not torment yourself with the horrors of the past. What happened has happened, let it rest in the ground with the dead."
    new "Dear, do not torment yourself with the horrors of the past. What happened has happened, let it rest in the ground with the dead."

    old "Insist, ask Lady Carolyn about Thomas"
    new "Insist, ask Lady Carolyn about Thomas"

    old "No...I want to know. I owe him that."
    new "No...I want to know. I owe him that."

    old "Lady Carolyn gave her a pitied look."
    new "Lady Carolyn gave her a pitied look."

    old "Well, when you dissapeared, your brother was desperate to find you. The guards turned the castle inside out."
    new "Well, when you dissapeared, your brother was desperate to find you. The guards turned the castle inside out."

    old "We kept holding our council meetings, but the truth was, your brother was often distracted, if he was even there at all."
    new "We kept holding our council meetings, but the truth was, your brother was often distracted, if he was even there at all."

    old "He wandered the castle, alone. He was never a tall boy, but he seemed to shrink even more."
    new "He wandered the castle, alone. He was never a tall boy, but he seemed to shrink even more."

    old "I had already left before Rosanna fell to the tribes, but before I left he had retreated to his room and rarely left at all."
    new "I had already left before Rosanna fell to the tribes, but before I left he had retreated to his room and rarely left at all."

    old "Lady Carolyn looked at Sarah, as if regretting that she would say this."
    new "Lady Carolyn looked at Sarah, as if regretting that she would say this."

    old "Dear, it pains me to say such cruelties to you, but I fear that when you left him, a part of him broke."
    new "Dear, it pains me to say such cruelties to you, but I fear that when you left him, a part of him broke."

    old "Sarah fought back the tears."
    new "Sarah fought back the tears."

    old "She had always known and lived with her betrayal to her brother. But to some degree, it had always been abstract."
    new "She had always known and lived with her betrayal to her brother. But to some degree, it had always been abstract."

    old "To now hear the stories of what her absence had caused..."
    new "To now hear the stories of what her absence had caused..."

    old "Sarah could feel the ground shift under het feet as the room began to spin."
    new "Sarah could feel the ground shift under het feet as the room began to spin."

    old "Closing her eyes, she commanded herself to be still."
    new "Closing her eyes, she commanded herself to be still."

    old "Slowly, her balance came back to her."
    new "Slowly, her balance came back to her."

    old "Opening her eyes, she could see only profound pity in Lady Carolyn's eyes."
    new "Opening her eyes, she could see only profound pity in Lady Carolyn's eyes."

    old "Relent, let the matter rest"
    new "Relent, let the matter rest"

    old "Sarah nodded her head. Lady Carolyn was right."
    new "Sarah nodded her head. Lady Carolyn was right."

    old "There was nothing but heartbreak going down that road."
    new "There was nothing but heartbreak going down that road."

    old "Sarah shook her head, hoping to rid herself of all of this."
    new "Sarah shook her head, hoping to rid herself of all of this."

    old "Mere moment ago her life had been in balance, her past a distant memory. Now a fragment of it was alive, standing in front of her."
    new "Mere moment ago her life had been in balance, her past a distant memory. Now a fragment of it was alive, standing in front of her."

    old "I...I was told to meet the master of the camp."
    new "I...I was told to meet the master of the camp."

    old "Lady Carolyn looked at Sarah, slightly puzzled."
    new "Lady Carolyn looked at Sarah, slightly puzzled."

    old "Ooh dear, I imagined you understood."
    new "Ooh dear, I imagined you understood."

    old "I am the master of the camp."
    new "I am the master of the camp."

    old "Sarah cursed herself for her foolishness. Why had she assumed the master would have to be a man?"
    new "Sarah cursed herself for her foolishness. Why had she assumed the master would have to be a man?"

    old "But, how? This is a Mythran army, and you..."
    new "But, how? This is a Mythran army, and you..."

    old "Lady Carolyn shrugged as she moved about the lavish tent."
    new "Lady Carolyn shrugged as she moved about the lavish tent."

    old "Mythra is a massive, sprawling empire. It had interests and concerns on every corner of the world."
    new "Mythra is a massive, sprawling empire. It had interests and concerns on every corner of the world."

    old "You don't get to a place like that by only sticking to your own."
    new "You don't get to a place like that by only sticking to your own."

    old "The Mythrans, they are not so concerned with who comes from where. They are rather a bit more practical."
    new "The Mythrans, they are not so concerned with who comes from where. They are rather a bit more practical."

    old "And I do have some talents they valued."
    new "And I do have some talents they valued."

    old "Lady Carolyn winked at her as she spoke."
    new "Lady Carolyn winked at her as she spoke."

    old "Sarah remembered Lady Carolyn as a skilled political operator. Experienced in both the noble circles, as well as familiar with the merchant class."
    new "Sarah remembered Lady Carolyn as a skilled political operator. Experienced in both the noble circles, as well as familiar with the merchant class."

    old "She moved about her designs in a way that seemed natural and proper, where others often seemed crude and greedy."
    new "She moved about her designs in a way that seemed natural and proper, where others often seemed crude and greedy."

    old "She managed all this as a woman, in Rosannan society, which heavily favored men for those types of positions of power."
    new "She managed all this as a woman, in Rosannan society, which heavily favored men for those types of positions of power."

    old "Of course, Sarah realized."
    new "Of course, Sarah realized."

    old "Of course a woman like her would be able to recover from the fall of Rosanna and remake herself."
    new "Of course a woman like her would be able to recover from the fall of Rosanna and remake herself."

    old "So you are a general now?"
    new "So you are a general now?"

    old "Me, a general? Ooh dear, I fear that if I were to pick up a sword I'd be a danger to myself more than anyone else."
    new "Me, a general? Ooh dear, I fear that if I were to pick up a sword I'd be a danger to myself more than anyone else."

    old "Again, Sarah saw her eyes flash across her body, inspecting her."
    new "Again, Sarah saw her eyes flash across her body, inspecting her."

    old "Not like you though."
    new "Not like you though."

    old "Look at that body, that stance. Every part of you screams the soldier."
    new "Look at that body, that stance. Every part of you screams the soldier."

    old "It is that I see so much of your family in your face, or I would never have recognized you to be the girl from all those years ago."
    new "It is that I see so much of your family in your face, or I would never have recognized you to be the girl from all those years ago."

    old "Sarah stared back at her."
    new "Sarah stared back at her."

    old "I'm not that girl anymore."
    new "I'm not that girl anymore."

    old "You're right about that. Very much a woman now."
    new "You're right about that. Very much a woman now."

    old "She smiled mischievously as she said it."
    new "She smiled mischievously as she said it."

    old "Sarah felt herself suddenly uncomfortable, oddly exposed and seen by one of the rare few people that still knew the old her."
    new "Sarah felt herself suddenly uncomfortable, oddly exposed and seen by one of the rare few people that still knew the old her."

    old "She had to push back, not let her get the better of her."
    new "She had to push back, not let her get the better of her."

    old "What are you to the Mythrans then?"
    new "What are you to the Mythrans then?"

    old "An agent."
    new "An agent."

    old "I made myself valuable in the capital, Rahayal, and after a while they saw my value, what I could bring. A certain degree of skill and discretion."
    new "I made myself valuable in the capital, Rahayal, and after a while they saw my value, what I could bring. A certain degree of skill and discretion."

    old "Lady Carolyn pushed a few scrolls aside as she leaned against the edge of the table."
    new "Lady Carolyn pushed a few scrolls aside as she leaned against the edge of the table."

    old "Soldiers, generals. They're all good at smashing things up. And Mythran armies are certainly very good at that."
    new "Soldiers, generals. They're all good at smashing things up. And Mythran armies are certainly very good at that."

    old "But sometimes, a softer touch is required. Not just someone who can use force, but someone who knows when to use it."
    new "But sometimes, a softer touch is required. Not just someone who can use force, but someone who knows when to use it."

    old "So what is this army doing out here then?"
    new "So what is this army doing out here then?"

    old "Aah, should I give up my secrets so easily to you?"
    new "Aah, should I give up my secrets so easily to you?"

    old "Assert yourself"
    new "Assert yourself"

    old "Sarah took a step foward, closing the distance between them."
    new "Sarah took a step foward, closing the distance between them."

    old "My father is dead. My brother is dead. But the crown still lives and it weighs on my head, even if you cannot bring yourself to see it."
    new "My father is dead. My brother is dead. But the crown still lives and it weighs on my head, even if you cannot bring yourself to see it."

    old "Sarah could see a sudden moment of doubt in Lady Carolyn's face."
    new "Sarah could see a sudden moment of doubt in Lady Carolyn's face."

    old "Tell me, Lady Carolyn."
    new "Tell me, Lady Carolyn."

    old "Are you still a patriot to the cause of our nation, or have you forsaken it for playing games with the Mythrans?"
    new "Are you still a patriot to the cause of our nation, or have you forsaken it for playing games with the Mythrans?"

    old "Lady Carolyn was quiet for a moment, considering her answer."
    new "Lady Carolyn was quiet for a moment, considering her answer."

    old "Sarah knew that she didn't have the power to compel an answer from Lady Carolyn."
    new "Sarah knew that she didn't have the power to compel an answer from Lady Carolyn."

    old "She lowered her head, looking at the ground like a misbehaved child."
    new "She lowered her head, looking at the ground like a misbehaved child."

    old "I have wandered the world for years."
    new "I have wandered the world for years."

    old "I stopped asking the question about where I was going a long time ago."
    new "I stopped asking the question about where I was going a long time ago."

    old "She looked up at Lady Carolyn, pleading for mercy with her eyes. She imagined she found it."
    new "She looked up at Lady Carolyn, pleading for mercy with her eyes. She imagined she found it."

    old "I need to understand what I'm doing here, so that I can begin to understand where I'm going."
    new "I need to understand what I'm doing here, so that I can begin to understand where I'm going."

    old "Where do your loyalties lie?"
    new "Where do your loyalties lie?"

    old "Then she spoke."
    new "Then she spoke."

    old "You bear a crown that none can see."
    new "You bear a crown that none can see."

    old "And I in turn bear my loyalties where none may see them."
    new "And I in turn bear my loyalties where none may see them."

    old "I am loyal to your family."
    new "I am loyal to your family."

    old "She was not sure if Lady Carolyn meant a word of it, but to even speak such a thing had meaning in itself."
    new "She was not sure if Lady Carolyn meant a word of it, but to even speak such a thing had meaning in itself."

    old "Good, then tell me why you are here. Why I am here."
    new "Good, then tell me why you are here. Why I am here."

    old "The why of it will be a longer story, I fear, best saved for tonight."
    new "The why of it will be a longer story, I fear, best saved for tonight."

    old "But you are here because I asked for you."
    new "But you are here because I asked for you."

    old "You asked for me?"
    new "You asked for me?"

    old "Your reputation has grown and grown over the years. The stories of the Rose Knight, a blonde haired woman who fights like a demon."
    new "Your reputation has grown and grown over the years. The stories of the Rose Knight, a blonde haired woman who fights like a demon."

    old "It was almost a year ago when I first heard the rumors and I began to suspect that you might still live."
    new "It was almost a year ago when I first heard the rumors and I began to suspect that you might still live."

    old "I could not move too directly."
    new "I could not move too directly."

    old "I was still in the capital of Rahayal. That city has more spies and wandering eyes than any other in the world."
    new "I was still in the capital of Rahayal. That city has more spies and wandering eyes than any other in the world."

    old "If I had called on you, many wonder what business I had with a random mercenary."
    new "If I had called on you, many wonder what business I had with a random mercenary."

    old "They would know that I came from Rosanna. They would know of you. And they would sooner put the two together."
    new "They would know that I came from Rosanna. They would know of you. And they would sooner put the two together."

    old "In Rahayal, I have a measure of influence, but I am a small fish in a great pond of many sharks."
